President Trump announced his nomination of Judge Brett Kavanaugh to replace Justice Anthony Kennedy on the Supreme Court. In his speech, Trump praised Kavanaugh's impeccable credentials, qualifications, and commitment to equal justice under the law. Kavanaugh, currently a judge on the D.C. Circuit Court of Appeals, is widely regarded as a brilliant jurist and a thought leader among his peers. He has authored over 300 opinions, with more than a dozen being adopted by the Supreme Court as the law of the land. Kavanaugh, in his response, expressed his gratitude to President Trump and his commitment to interpreting the law as written and preserving the Constitution. He emphasized the importance of an independent judiciary and pledged to keep an open mind in every case. Kavanaugh's nomination now awaits confirmation by the Senate.